<subSubSection id="C3196578FF95FFC45C89FA018A2109FC" pageId="4" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF95FFC45C89FA018A2109FC" blockId="4.[166,1225,1258,1510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be easily recognized from having patterned wing (
<figureCitation id="13382A76FF95FFC458D5FA018ABD099C" box="[1159,1219,1419,1446]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[240,1131,825,1695]" captionTargetId="figure-293@3.[240,1134,811,1710]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Prochyliza nigrimana (1), Protopiophila latipes (2), Stearibia nigriceps (3–4), and Neottiophilum praeustum (5): 1, 3 — habitus, left; 2, 4 — head and mesonotum, dorsal, 5 — wing. Рис. 3. Prochyliza nigrimana (1), Protopiophila latipes (2), Stearibia nigriceps (3–4) и Neottiophilum praeustum (5): 1, 3 — общий вид, слева; 2, 4 — голова и среднеспинка, сверху; 5 — крыло." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412923/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B977EAE1FF95FFC45CF4FA218ECA09FF" box="[166,180,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">5</emphasis>
) with vein R 
<subScript id="178734B6FF95FFC45D19FA348F2D09F6" attach="left" box="[331,339,1470,1484]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">1</subScript>
setulose apically, and presence of three or four katepisternal setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
